rComments: The worst professor ever.  The only way to stay awake is to count how many times he says "uhh" at the beginning of a sentence.  The tests were a joke, and the study guide was useless.

Quite possibly the worst professor ever. I emailed him a simple question that I needed clarification on and he simply told me, "I said this in class". Well, I am sorry I forgot and wanted to make sure. His powerpoints are totally useless and his study guides are insane. They take forever to go through and 80% of the stuff isn't even on the exam.

If you like Asian history, then this is a fun class. It may be boring at times, but, again, its interesting if you like the topic. Also, there is a lot of reading (1 text book and 5 novels). Get a good TA (pray for Troy) and you should be fine. If you do the work, then you'll get an A.

This is the worst professor I have ever had.  No reason to go to class except that he takes attendance every time.  Lectures consist of generally around 80 powerpoint slides filled with either text or useless pictures.  Terrible lecturer also.  He gives out a study guide before the exams and if you go through that you should get a B.  Avoid class!

Good thing he takes attendance, otherwise no one would go to his lecture.  The best part of said lecture is looking around and counting the people sleeping so hard their mouth is hanging open.  One lecture was nothing but him reading parts of the Tao Te Ching off of powerpoint slides.  Pray for a good TA.

Worst speaker there is and doesn't teach anything relevant to the test.
 His syllabus is extremely outdated and disorganized. I missed a couple things that I shouldn't have because they were not on the syllabus.
 Easy class though.
The class is easy, but extremely unorganized. He knows his material, but is just flat horrible.
We basically had one assignment the entire semester and he actually told us that we could only get two grades, an A or a B.  He was a really cool guy but his classes were boring.

yeah. last year we had class downstairs at KAMs and it was really crowded. As long as you sit next to/behind someone who is smart, you will do good on your tests. And yes, you get a terms sheet before the final so you dont even need to keep up w/ readings. Crapy lecturer. Boring classes. TA's were ok. dont take his class, no benefits whatsoever.

In all honesty, Toby is by far the worst professor that I have ever had at this university.  His lectures are incredibly difficult to follow, tests are terribly obscure with little direction as to what to study, and he is completely unresponsive to the needs and concerns of his students.

Toby is the kind of professor that would be awesome if he didn't have to grade work. He's a nice guy, but extremely unorganized (his syllabus is useless), difficult to reach outside of class, and angers easily when asked questions about assignments.
worst teacher ever.....totally arogant...has no idea how to convey all the information he knows

lectures do not correspond to the tests at all.  as long as u study for the tests this class doesn't require a whole lot of work.  u really don't need to read cause they give u a review sheet at the end.  id's are really obscure.
